09/07/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul denounced on Sunday (July 8th) the deadly insurgent attack on a crowded market in Armili, Iraq, populated mainly by ethnic Turkoman Shi'ites. Saturday's truck bombing killed at least 150 people and wounded 250 others. More than 20 of them were flown to Turkey for medical treatment. (Zaman, Hurriyet, NTV, EuroNews, UPI - 09/07/07; Anadolu Agency - 08/07/07) 
